nded in  by woltman tietjen’s father richard woltman currently girard’s chairman emeritus of the board the senior woltman a pioneer in the independent brokerdealer industry in  founded the predecessor firm of first allied securities which is now owned by rcap woltman and his wife kaye later acquired and merged spelman  co inc and sentra securities corp eventually selling to sunamerica inc kaye woltman passed away in  woltman tietjen was not immediately available but in an interview last april with financial advisor she stressed the importance of personal relationships with advisors “bigger isn’t always better” for an independent firm she told fa “it just depends on how bigger is structured bigger can be better if the large entity understands the important of the service component and the relationship component” one advantage larger firms offer is a bigger pool of potential partners for succession planning purposes woltman tietjen told the magazine in todays statement she said the sale to rcap will provide “greater opportunities for our advisors and a more diverse service offering” girard and vsr will be joining rcap’s conglomeration of brokerdealers that operate as cetera financial group the group includes cetera advisors cetera advisor networks cetera financial institutions cetera financial specialists first allied securities the legend group investors capital corp jp turner  company and summit financial services group to read more stories  click here loading other articles loading other articles « previous article  next article »  comments login in order to post a comment quick poll whom would you like to see president trump pick as chair of the federal reserve gary cohn janet yellen neither of the above view results home login about us media kit ftp site subscriptions reprints contact us sitemap privacy policy  terms and conditions   charter financial publishing network inc all rights reserved girard securities inc girard securities inc client portal  advisor por